For this reason, kernels have been recently used to develop innovative approaches to relation extraction based on syntactic information, in which the examples preserve their original representations (i.e. parse trees) and are compared by the kernel function (Zelenko et al. , 2003; Culotta and Sorensen, 2004; Zhao and Grishman, 2005). 
